stories.text:
As the end of the year approaches I took time to reflect. I couldn't finish all that I planned. Therefore I need to prioritize going forward. Somethings are easy to argue for. I.e. look at used techstacks and how they work together (React, FastAPI, sqlalchemy).

Now my question: With experience, what do you think is important as a software developer. What is something that juniors are often not aware off. Something they don't know they don't know?

stories.text:
Hi HN! It's time for end-of-year giving, and I'm always looking for charitable causes that will put my money to good use. What nonprofits do you support?

Personally, I like GiveDirectly—their work is research-backed and life-changing—and if you're interested in donating to them I'd appreciate if you did so through my weird little romantic art project (100% of your donation goes to GiveDirectly): https://helpmepropose.live

I'd love to learn about other great organizations!
stories.title: Ask HN: What nonprofits do you donate to?
